FBIS4-45097 "jpnea034___94046" JPRS-NEA-94-034 JPRS Near East & South Asia 8 May 1994 SOUTH ASIA IRAN Discarded Cigarette Ignites Polluted River Discarded Cigarette Ignites Polluted River 94LA0178G Tehran JAHAN-E ESLAM in Persian 8 May 94 p 3 94LA0178G Tehran JAHAN-E ESLAM Persian CSO [Text] Petroleum products and flammable materials in the Siyahrud River in Qa'emshahr caused a fire on this river Friday. Mohammad 'Ali Lotfi, a fire-fighting official in Qa'emshahr, said: The petroleum products came into this river via the sewage channels from Textile Factory No. 1. He added: The fire started when someone passing by threw his cigarette flame into the river. Lotfi said: The fire immediately covered a large part of the river with 20-meter flames. He added: The fire was put out by fire-fighting officials, and the petroleum products were also cleaned out of the river.
